  "type": "Eco.Gameplay.Civics.Laws.Law",
  "name": "[C] Tax Legislation",
  "reference": false,
  "description": "All taxes on White Tiger have to fulfill certain requirements. Taxes not fulfilling these requirements are invalid and their collection is not lawful.\u000bAll the constitutional requirements on laws also apply to taxes, this only adds additional requirements.\u000bThese requirements are as follows:\u000b\u000b1. the tax may not simply forget a person being unable to pay, the amount must be remembered and charged at a later time.\n2. the tax may not block actions when being unable to pay.\n3. the tax has to provide reporting to both citizens and the government. This reporting has to include how much of this specific tax was paid by the citizen in the last 24h and in total, as well as how much was paid for this tax by all citizens together in the last 24h and in total. The reporting also has to inform citizens of how much money they still owe to this tax.\u000b4. charging taxes through this tax has to be compatible to the constitutional federal tax reporting inside this law, which collects information on how much tax income the government received in both the last 24h and in total. This can be easily achieved by using the \"smart\" tax actions.\n5. if the tax acts on a timer (e.g. a wealth tax), the timer has to be at least as long as the \"active\" duration (48h) so every active player has the chance to login at least once during every tax cycle.",
